### ============================================================================
### AUTHENTICATION TESTS
### ============================================================================

### 1. Register Jimmy Kimunyi
# Expected: 201 Created (first time) or 409 Conflict (if already exists)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "{{name}}",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 2. Test duplicate registration (should return 409 Conflict)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "{{name}}",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### 3. Test invalid registration - missing fields (should return 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}"
}

### ============================================================================
### BROWSER-BASED LOGIN (Required for authenticated requests)
### ============================================================================

### 4. Login via Browser UI
# Step 1: Open this URL in your browser: {{webUrl}}/auth/login
# Step 2: Enter credentials:
#         Email: {{email}}
#         Password: {{password}}
# Step 3: After login, open DevTools > Application > Cookies
# Step 4: Copy the value of 'authjs.session-token' cookie
# Step 5: Update @sessionToken variable above with the copied value

### ============================================================================
### PATIENT MANAGEMENT (Requires Authentication)
### ============================================================================

### 5. Get all patients
GET {{baseUrl}}/patients
Cookie: authjs.session-token={{sessionToken}}

### 6. Create a new patient
# @name createPatient
POST {{baseUrl}}/patients
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: authjs.session-token={{sessionToken}}

{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "email": "jane.doe@example.com",
  "phone": "+1-555-123-4567",
  "dateOfBirth": "1985-03-15",
  "gender": "FEMALE",
  "medicalRecordNumber": "MRN-12345",
  "notes": "Patient has history of diabetes"
}

### 7. Get a specific patient
GET {{baseUrl}}/patients/{{patientId}}
Cookie: authjs.session-token={{sessionToken}}

### 8. Update a patient
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/patients/{{patientId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: authjs.session-token={{sessionToken}}

{
  "name": "Jane Doe Updated",
  "notes": "Updated patient information"
}

### 9. Delete a patient
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/patients/{{patientId}}
Cookie: authjs.session-token={{sessionToken}}

### ============================================================================
### FILE MANAGEMENT (Requires Authentication)
### ============================================================================

### 10. Get all files
GET {{baseUrl}}/files
Cookie: authjs.session-token={{sessionToken}}

### 11. Get all files for a specific patient
GET {{baseUrl}}/files?patientId={{patientId}}
Cookie: authjs.session-token={{sessionToken}}

### 12. Upload a file (Note: Use UI or Postman for actual file upload)
# For file upload, use the UI at {{webUrl}}/dashboard/files/upload
# Or use Postman/Insomnia with multipart/form-data
POST {{baseUrl}}/files
Content-Type: multipart/form-data
Cookie: authjs.session-token={{sessionToken}}

# FormData fields:
# - file: [binary file]
# - patientId: {{patientId}}

### 13. Get a specific file
GET {{baseUrl}}/files/{{fileId}}
Cookie: authjs.session-token={{sessionToken}}

### 14. Delete a file
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/files/{{fileId}}
Cookie: authjs.session-token={{sessionToken}}

### ============================================================================
### AI ANALYSIS (Requires Authentication)
### ============================================================================

### 15. Analyze a file (stub implementation)
POST {{baseUrl}}/analyze
Content-Type: application/json
Cookie: authjs.session-token={{sessionToken}}

{
  "fileId": "{{fileId}}",
  "inferenceType": "csv-analysis",
  "inputData": {
    "columns": ["column1", "column2"]
  }
}

### 16. Get all inferences
GET {{baseUrl}}/analyze
Cookie: authjs.session-token={{sessionToken}}

### 17. Get inferences for a specific patient
GET {{baseUrl}}/analyze?patientId={{patientId}}
Cookie: authjs.session-token={{sessionToken}}

### 18. Get inferences for a specific file
GET {{baseUrl}}/analyze?fileId={{fileId}}
Cookie: authjs.session-token={{sessionToken}}

### ============================================================================
### TESTING NOTES
### ============================================================================
###
### Quick Test Flow:
### 1. Run test #1 to register (or confirm user exists)
### 2. Follow test #4 to login via browser and get session token
### 3. Update @sessionToken variable with your actual token
### 4. Run test #6 to create a patient, copy the patient ID from response
### 5. Update @patientId variable
### 6. Use the UI to upload a file, then get the file ID
### 7. Update @fileId variable
### 8. Now you can test all endpoints!
###
### Alternative: Use the web UI for easier testing:
### - Dashboard: {{webUrl}}/dashboard
### - Patients: {{webUrl}}/dashboard/patients
### - Files: {{webUrl}}/dashboard/files
###
